WEBVTT

00:00:00.040 --> 00:00:14.740
(Watch on KonFlix.vip)

00:00:04.805 --> 00:00:07.941
TORINNER, the popular K-pop group
that created a sensation

00:00:08.008 --> 00:00:10.110
right after their debut in Korea

00:00:10.177 --> 00:00:12.279
has arrived in Japan
to make their debut

00:00:12.379 --> 00:00:15.015
and capture the hearts
of Japanese ladies.

00:00:15.115 --> 00:00:17.017
- Congratulations!
- Congratulations!

00:00:17.084 --> 00:00:20.220
Yes! I got the last autographed one!

00:00:20.287 --> 00:00:21.555
- Gosh!
- First of all

00:00:21.655 --> 00:00:23.524
Ryo is so handsome
that I'm overwhelmed.

00:00:23.624 --> 00:00:25.425
His existence is a miracle,
and he's precious!

00:00:26.393 --> 00:00:28.128
TORINNER, congratulations
on your debut in Japan!

00:00:28.195 --> 00:00:29.796
Ms. Park Ji-soo is our goddess!

00:00:29.863 --> 00:00:32.799
- Rich agencies sure are flashy.
- You gave us a reason to live!

00:00:32.866 --> 00:00:35.135
Why are you talking like
it's none of your concern, idiot?

00:00:35.235 --> 00:00:36.537
MUST GET FIRST PLACE
IN DEBUT SONG RANKING

00:00:36.637 --> 00:00:37.838
According to my research

00:00:37.905 --> 00:00:39.373
the groups that can't get first place

00:00:39.439 --> 00:00:40.474
in the debut ranking

00:00:40.541 --> 00:00:42.676
only have a survival rate of 18%!

00:00:43.076 --> 00:00:46.513
Which means I can't pay off my debt
unless we get first place!

00:00:46.613 --> 00:00:47.915
My debt is five billion won.

00:00:48.415 --> 00:00:50.484
That's about 500 million yen.

00:00:50.584 --> 00:00:52.352
There's no way I can pay that off!

00:00:52.419 --> 00:00:54.388
In any case, do everything it takes
to defeat TORINNER

00:00:54.454 --> 00:00:56.924
and get us first place,
or my life will be over!

00:00:56.990 --> 00:00:59.259
Japanese fans have more love
and respect for artists

00:00:59.359 --> 00:01:01.061
- than anyone else in the world.
- Ouch.

00:01:01.128 --> 00:01:02.596
That's why I believe that

00:01:02.696 --> 00:01:05.098
Japan should be the first choice
in their worldwide debut.

00:01:05.165 --> 00:01:07.100
- She doesn't think that.
- Please root for them.

00:01:07.167 --> 00:01:08.569
That darn woman!

00:01:09.736 --> 00:01:10.837
I'm going out for coffee.

00:01:12.272 --> 00:01:13.607
She makes a lot of noise.

00:01:20.314 --> 00:01:22.583
They're getting on my nerves!

00:01:30.424 --> 00:01:33.026
Are they debt collectors?

00:01:45.706 --> 00:01:47.140
Let's sort it out first.

00:01:47.741 --> 00:01:50.711
To survive, I need to pay off
the 500 million yen debt.

00:01:50.777 --> 00:01:52.379
That means NAZE's debut song

00:01:52.446 --> 00:01:53.447
must rank first.

00:01:53.513 --> 00:01:54.514
In other words

00:01:54.581 --> 00:01:55.983
they must defeat TORINNER.

00:01:56.049 --> 00:01:57.751
For that to happen,
I need a promotional budget

00:01:57.818 --> 00:01:58.852
bigger than TORINNER's.

00:01:58.919 --> 00:02:00.921
But I have no money!

00:02:00.988 --> 00:02:03.991
That means I'm doomed!

00:02:06.159 --> 00:02:08.395
What should I do?

00:02:22.275 --> 00:02:23.844
How tasteless.

00:02:27.581 --> 00:02:32.052
We successfully made a big splash
in Japan, thanks to you. Thank--

00:02:32.119 --> 00:02:33.387
I heard that Azuma's group

00:02:33.487 --> 00:02:36.056
achieved great success at that event.

00:02:37.524 --> 00:02:40.560
No, the streaming numbers
for our group are overwhelmingly--

00:02:40.661 --> 00:02:42.663
People are talking about it
in Korea, too.

00:02:43.096 --> 00:02:45.932
They want to know about the group
that suddenly appeared in Japan.

00:02:47.067 --> 00:02:48.235
I am sorry.

00:02:48.769 --> 00:02:52.039
But a minor agency like that could
never manage a large-scale promotion.

00:02:52.606 --> 00:02:53.674
No need to worry--

00:02:53.774 --> 00:02:55.442
You lied to me.

00:03:00.814 --> 00:03:03.350
Do you remember what you promised?

00:03:03.950 --> 00:03:04.951
You said you would

00:03:06.253 --> 00:03:08.055
crush Azuma's group
before their debut.

00:03:12.192 --> 00:03:14.594
Yes. Certainly, sir.

00:03:14.995 --> 00:03:16.663
It's a huge gathering
of handsome idols!

00:03:16.730 --> 00:03:19.700
Welcome to the Mid-winter Sports Day!

00:03:19.800 --> 00:03:21.601
HOT IDOLS ASSEMBLE!
MID-WINTER SPORTS DAY

00:03:21.702 --> 00:03:23.270
We have TORINNER,
the up-and-coming rookies

00:03:23.336 --> 00:03:24.471
and 4orce, the talk of the town...

00:03:24.571 --> 00:03:26.473
as well as other groups
on the verge of their next big break

00:03:26.573 --> 00:03:30.544
who will be engaging
in heated battles!

00:03:30.610 --> 00:03:32.045
Cut! Okay!

00:03:32.112 --> 00:03:33.980
Everyone,
please run through the rehearsal.

00:03:34.081 --> 00:03:35.382
- Yes!
- Yes!

00:03:35.482 --> 00:03:36.483
Go!

00:03:40.721 --> 00:03:42.322
- All right.
- I'm scared!

00:03:42.389 --> 00:03:45.425
Guys! This is our chance
to make NAZE's name known!

00:03:45.525 --> 00:03:47.461
Make sure
you promote yourselves well!

00:03:47.561 --> 00:03:50.664
Why are we having a sports day
when it's freezing?

00:03:50.731 --> 00:03:52.999
- The short sleeves are killing me.
- Don't complain!

00:03:53.100 --> 00:03:55.702
You need to be seen
as much as possible before you debut.

00:03:56.536 --> 00:03:58.105
Get your game faces on.

00:03:58.171 --> 00:04:00.607
I will crush you this time.

00:04:00.674 --> 00:04:02.709
Good morning, Ms. Tomiko!

00:04:02.776 --> 00:04:04.311
- Good morning!
- Morning.

00:04:04.411 --> 00:04:06.646
It's cold,
so don't push yourselves too hard.

00:04:06.713 --> 00:04:10.450
I am going
to make you all into stars.

00:04:10.550 --> 00:04:11.585
- Thank you!
- Thank you!

00:04:12.185 --> 00:04:14.054
- Continue.
- Let's begin with

00:04:14.154 --> 00:04:18.358
the inter-group dodgeball tournament!

00:04:20.127 --> 00:04:22.763
Okay, let the game begin!

00:04:29.002 --> 00:04:31.605
NAZE has been hit again!

00:04:31.671 --> 00:04:34.674
- That lady looks intimidating.
- Go!

00:04:35.075 --> 00:04:37.911
That's Kira Tomiko,
the chairwoman of Kira Production.

00:04:37.978 --> 00:04:40.247
She's the Empress
of Japanese Showbiz.

00:04:40.313 --> 00:04:41.314
Good!

00:04:41.381 --> 00:04:43.183
Gosh. So, she's powerful?

00:04:43.250 --> 00:04:45.886
She has produced many famous
and popular actors and celebrities

00:04:45.952 --> 00:04:47.921
in the past 20 years.

00:04:47.988 --> 00:04:49.256
Twenty years?

00:04:50.257 --> 00:04:51.291
Hang on.

00:04:51.525 --> 00:04:55.529
Do you mean that Japanese Empress
is promoting that new group?

00:04:56.163 --> 00:04:57.931
This is bad! They're strong rivals!

00:04:57.998 --> 00:05:01.268
Don't get started on that.
Everyone here is our rival.

00:05:01.868 --> 00:05:04.538
So, they are all rivals getting
in my way of paying off my debt?

00:05:05.639 --> 00:05:08.775
Guys! Promote yourselves harder!

00:05:08.842 --> 00:05:10.977
- Ms. Nam!
- Okay!

00:05:11.044 --> 00:05:12.479
Mr. Azuma, please stop her!

00:05:12.546 --> 00:05:13.647
Ms. Nam.

00:05:14.514 --> 00:05:16.183
You're doing well today.

00:05:16.249 --> 00:05:18.051
My, Ms. Park!

00:05:18.151 --> 00:05:20.787
Thank you for the live performance
the other day.

00:05:21.221 --> 00:05:23.156
To show my appreciation...

00:05:24.524 --> 00:05:25.525
There you go.

00:05:25.625 --> 00:05:26.960
TRAITOR

00:05:27.027 --> 00:05:28.361
Poverty...

00:05:28.662 --> 00:05:30.530
makes one poor in the heart, too.

00:05:31.531 --> 00:05:33.800
- It's unpleasant.
- What did you say?

00:05:35.535 --> 00:05:37.204
Forgive me.

00:05:37.270 --> 00:05:41.775
I transferred TORINNER
to Bouquet Music

00:05:41.842 --> 00:05:44.211
to provide the members
with support worthy of their talents.

00:05:44.744 --> 00:05:47.514
A poor agency would make
their future uncertain.

00:05:47.614 --> 00:05:50.450
Are you picking a fight?
You betrayed me!

00:05:50.550 --> 00:05:53.320
Shouldn't you apologize
for your betrayal first?

00:05:53.753 --> 00:05:56.356
People should support each other...

00:05:56.423 --> 00:05:59.492
- like this!
- Ms. Nam! They're recording!

00:05:59.593 --> 00:06:01.728
We're recording. Please be quiet!

00:06:01.795 --> 00:06:03.196
I am so sorry!

00:06:03.663 --> 00:06:06.299
Isn't she the CEO of NAZE
that the gossip magazine wrote about?

00:06:06.900 --> 00:06:09.603
"CEO of NAZE's agency
Causes a Scene at the Airport!"

00:06:10.337 --> 00:06:12.505
Film her. It's funny.

00:06:12.572 --> 00:06:13.607
Very well, then.

00:06:13.707 --> 00:06:17.110
In that case, let's settle this
fairly through work.

00:06:17.544 --> 00:06:18.545
Bring it on!

00:06:18.645 --> 00:06:20.814
Money is the only thing
you can rely on.

00:06:21.081 --> 00:06:22.449
I won't be defeated
by someone like you!

00:06:24.050 --> 00:06:25.185
Well, then...

00:06:26.253 --> 00:06:27.587
Let's compete on the number

00:06:27.654 --> 00:06:30.156
of social media followers
that TORINNER and NAZE have.

00:06:30.724 --> 00:06:32.425
We'll compare the results
in two weeks.

00:06:32.592 --> 00:06:35.695
The loser will grant a wish
to the winner.

00:06:35.996 --> 00:06:37.330
Anything.

00:06:37.430 --> 00:06:39.799
Excellent! Challenge accepted!

00:06:39.866 --> 00:06:41.301
Hey... What are you talking about?

00:06:41.401 --> 00:06:43.770
No, Ms. Nam! Please take it back.

00:06:45.038 --> 00:06:48.341
Well then, let's both fight fair.

00:06:51.344 --> 00:06:52.712
Take that back.

00:06:53.313 --> 00:06:54.614
- It's not too late yet.
- Nice!

00:06:54.714 --> 00:06:57.250
Isn't this turning out to be
a very realistic reality show?

00:06:57.751 --> 00:06:59.085
Right?

00:06:59.185 --> 00:07:00.954
She's hopelessly stupid.

00:07:01.021 --> 00:07:02.889
This is the best content
I could ever wish for.

00:07:03.356 --> 00:07:06.760
Please let us announce the results
on our show.

00:07:07.193 --> 00:07:08.395
My pleasure.

00:07:08.461 --> 00:07:10.230
By the way,
what will you do if you win?

00:07:10.297 --> 00:07:11.898
Well, for now...

00:07:12.399 --> 00:07:15.802
I'll do my best to win this contest.

00:07:16.069 --> 00:07:18.338
- I'll be rooting for you.
- Thank you.

00:07:19.606 --> 00:07:21.508
- What?
- Look at this.

00:07:22.943 --> 00:07:25.578
- What's this?
- NAZE's sticker old hag

00:07:25.645 --> 00:07:27.580
picked a fight
with Ms. Park this time.

00:07:28.715 --> 00:07:31.318
NAZE's live performance
was good, but...

00:07:31.384 --> 00:07:33.787
We have to root for TORINNER, right?

00:07:33.853 --> 00:07:35.889
Ladies, contact everyone you know!

00:07:35.956 --> 00:07:36.957
- Yes!
- Okay!

00:07:37.057 --> 00:07:38.892
Are you stupid?

00:07:38.992 --> 00:07:41.027
TORINNER already made
their debut in Korea

00:07:41.094 --> 00:07:43.229
and they have
over a million followers!

00:07:43.296 --> 00:07:45.165
On the other hand,
we have less than 100,000.

00:07:45.231 --> 00:07:46.399
How do we even compete?

00:07:46.499 --> 00:07:49.436
But it got on my nerves
when she said that.

00:07:49.536 --> 00:07:52.973
Even so, how could you promise
to do anything she says?

00:07:53.073 --> 00:07:55.108
You fell right into her trap!

00:07:55.175 --> 00:07:58.478
She might tell us
to retire right away.

00:07:58.545 --> 00:08:00.513
I am really sorry!

00:08:00.613 --> 00:08:02.248
I'm done with this!

00:08:02.749 --> 00:08:05.218
Hey, don't just stand there.
Go to practice.

00:08:05.285 --> 00:08:06.586
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir.

00:08:13.526 --> 00:08:15.795
Hello, this is Nam Entertainment.

00:08:15.862 --> 00:08:19.132
I'm Kira Tomiko from Kira Production.

00:08:19.566 --> 00:08:21.334
Kira Pro... What?

00:08:22.502 --> 00:08:23.770
That huge talent agency?

00:08:23.837 --> 00:08:25.171
Are you Ms. Nam?

00:08:25.271 --> 00:08:28.308
The row between you and Ms. Park
the other day

00:08:28.375 --> 00:08:30.010
must've been rough for you.

00:08:30.944 --> 00:08:34.581
Why don't you and I be friends?

00:08:42.455 --> 00:08:44.524
- One, two, three, four...
- One, two, three, four...

00:08:44.591 --> 00:08:48.294
What will happen to us
if we really lose?

00:08:48.728 --> 00:08:50.930
There's nothing we can do
if our boss is such a fool.

00:08:50.997 --> 00:08:52.899
Besides, it's already
all over the internet.

00:08:54.434 --> 00:08:56.469
There's no way we can win!

00:08:56.536 --> 00:08:58.938
To make things worse, we're going up
against that conniving Ms. Park.

00:08:59.539 --> 00:09:01.307
She'll definitely tell us
to retire at once.

00:09:02.008 --> 00:09:05.245
If that happens,
the boys will be left stranded.

00:09:05.845 --> 00:09:06.980
Is there a secret way

00:09:07.047 --> 00:09:10.183
to make
their follower count skyrocket?

00:09:11.051 --> 00:09:12.986
Or is the "genius" in your title
just for show?

00:09:13.053 --> 00:09:15.255
You know, you're starting
to sound like Nam lately.

00:09:16.222 --> 00:09:18.825
I wouldn't be racking my brains here
if I had a secret plan.

00:09:19.759 --> 00:09:22.962
There's nothing I can do this time.

00:09:23.630 --> 00:09:27.133
- One, two, three, four, five, six
- One, two, three, four, five, six

00:09:27.233 --> 00:09:31.404
- seven, eight. One, two, three...
- I need to do something for them.

00:09:31.471 --> 00:09:33.873
I didn't expect you
to visit in person.

00:09:33.973 --> 00:09:35.909
I'm sorry for dropping in.

00:09:36.843 --> 00:09:37.844
Excuse me...

00:09:39.179 --> 00:09:42.015
Our CEO can be
a little scatterbrained.

00:09:42.515 --> 00:09:44.984
I think she impulsively made
that promise

00:09:45.085 --> 00:09:46.719
but she's a good person at heart.

00:09:47.153 --> 00:09:50.523
She doesn't resent you anymore.

00:09:50.623 --> 00:09:52.425
Or rather, I won't let her.

00:09:52.826 --> 00:09:57.764
So, could you pretend that
the whole thing never happened?

00:10:05.205 --> 00:10:09.375
Around 40 K-pop groups
debut each year.

00:10:10.343 --> 00:10:14.280
Among them,
only 10% can make a living.

00:10:14.380 --> 00:10:17.383
You can't survive if you aren't
determined to win at all costs.

00:10:18.218 --> 00:10:22.455
I chose the biggest agency,
Bouquet Music, so I can survive.

00:10:24.224 --> 00:10:27.227
Funding, connections, facilities...

00:10:28.828 --> 00:10:31.531
They can provide the best support

00:10:31.598 --> 00:10:34.000
to develop the member's talents
in every aspect.

00:10:35.535 --> 00:10:37.837
My job is to protect the lives
of those boys.

00:10:38.771 --> 00:10:39.839
That's why

00:10:40.507 --> 00:10:42.008
if anyone gets in my way

00:10:42.775 --> 00:10:45.512
I'll crush them
by any means necessary.

00:10:50.650 --> 00:10:53.753
"I'll crush them
by any means necessary."

00:10:54.487 --> 00:10:55.922
That's what she said.

00:10:55.989 --> 00:10:59.792
Bring it on!
I'm going to crush you, too!

00:10:59.859 --> 00:11:01.294
How?

00:11:02.061 --> 00:11:05.899
Actually, I got a call today
from Kira Pro's president, Tomiko.

00:11:05.965 --> 00:11:08.067
The Empress of the Japanese Showbiz!

00:11:08.134 --> 00:11:11.404
The Empress invited me
to fight against TORINNER with her!

00:11:11.471 --> 00:11:14.807
A huge agency suddenly wants
to team up with small fry like us?

00:11:14.874 --> 00:11:15.875
That's fishy.

00:11:15.942 --> 00:11:17.977
There must be a catch. Drop it.

00:11:18.044 --> 00:11:22.148
It's okay. We have to bet
on this chance now!

00:11:26.753 --> 00:11:31.257
Their methods are so vulgar.

00:11:31.357 --> 00:11:35.495
They are just throwing money around
for big promotions.

00:11:35.562 --> 00:11:38.431
No matter how I look at it,
it's tasteless.

00:11:39.732 --> 00:11:42.268
But you're different, Ms. Nam.

00:11:42.335 --> 00:11:44.404
You had the courage
to come to Japan alone

00:11:44.904 --> 00:11:47.240
and the integrity to compete fairly.

00:11:47.707 --> 00:11:51.010
It's truly admirable!
It makes me respect you.

00:11:51.077 --> 00:11:52.078
To tell you the truth

00:11:52.145 --> 00:11:55.882
I was the one who discovered the boys
who debuted as TORINNER!

00:11:56.482 --> 00:11:59.686
I let Park Ji-soo produce them,
but she stole them away!

00:11:59.752 --> 00:12:01.821
My, is that so?

00:12:01.888 --> 00:12:04.123
How nasty!

00:12:04.190 --> 00:12:07.727
I loved them like my own children
and worked hard with them!

00:12:07.794 --> 00:12:10.230
The boys were deceived by Ms. Park.

00:12:10.296 --> 00:12:12.732
Oh, poor things!

00:12:13.466 --> 00:12:16.102
Go ahead, get it all off your chest.

00:12:16.169 --> 00:12:18.304
I'll be your listening ear.

00:12:18.404 --> 00:12:20.306
Thank you so much!

00:12:28.881 --> 00:12:30.550
I feel so much better.

00:12:31.618 --> 00:12:34.320
I'm sorry,
I keep talking about myself.

00:12:34.420 --> 00:12:37.156
You don't have
to worry about it at all.

00:12:38.424 --> 00:12:40.893
So, there's a Korean saying that goes

00:12:41.227 --> 00:12:45.431
"The crayfish is a friend
of the crab," right?

00:12:45.498 --> 00:12:46.799
That's me!

00:12:46.866 --> 00:12:49.235
When I see someone similar
to me in trouble

00:12:49.302 --> 00:12:52.739
I feel a strong urge to help them.

00:12:53.172 --> 00:12:55.308
So please let me support you.

00:12:55.375 --> 00:12:56.376
Okay!

00:12:58.077 --> 00:13:00.780
I don't want to lose.

00:13:01.180 --> 00:13:04.117
I want to give that scammer
a taste of her own medicine!

00:13:04.317 --> 00:13:06.219
Besides, the reason we're in Japan

00:13:06.286 --> 00:13:08.187
is because Park Ji-soo played dirty

00:13:08.288 --> 00:13:10.823
and gave us a hard time!

00:13:10.890 --> 00:13:13.593
There are so many more things
I want to tell you!

00:13:20.133 --> 00:13:21.501
What's this?

00:13:21.567 --> 00:13:22.735
No way!

00:13:24.671 --> 00:13:27.206
Good morning, everyone!

00:13:27.640 --> 00:13:31.678
Hey, you two! Stop acting lovey-dovey
at the office early in the morning.

00:13:31.744 --> 00:13:32.912
Since late last night

00:13:33.012 --> 00:13:34.347
gossip articles about TORINNER

00:13:34.414 --> 00:13:35.982
have been popping up.

00:13:36.049 --> 00:13:37.317
It even mentioned
that they were poached

00:13:37.383 --> 00:13:38.651
right before their debut.

00:13:38.751 --> 00:13:41.421
We were the only ones
who knew about this.

00:13:42.555 --> 00:13:43.856
That was what I said yesterday.

00:13:43.956 --> 00:13:45.525
So you do know something?

00:13:45.591 --> 00:13:47.894
What? No, I know nothing.

00:13:49.395 --> 00:13:52.899
Was this what she meant by
"the crayfish is the crab's friend?"

00:13:53.533 --> 00:13:54.634
Crayfish?

00:13:55.535 --> 00:13:57.370
It's nothing!

00:13:57.470 --> 00:14:00.573
Oh, right! We've run out
of toilet paper. I'll go buy some.

00:14:02.275 --> 00:14:04.077
PRESIDENT TOMIKO

00:14:10.483 --> 00:14:13.419
Your call cannot
be answered right now.

00:14:13.886 --> 00:14:15.655
Please leave a message...

00:14:15.722 --> 00:14:16.856
Well, who cares?

00:14:17.523 --> 00:14:18.858
It's not like I lied.

00:14:19.525 --> 00:14:21.828
- TORINNER is here!
- Ms. Park!

00:14:21.928 --> 00:14:23.496
Some articles say you poached

00:14:23.596 --> 00:14:26.999
TORINNER's members
from another agency. Is it true?

00:14:27.066 --> 00:14:28.935
We just transferred
to another agency.

00:14:29.268 --> 00:14:31.537
There was no improper deal.
Excuse me.

00:14:31.604 --> 00:14:34.340
There was an improper deal, right?

00:14:34.407 --> 00:14:35.608
Can you answer our questions?

00:14:35.708 --> 00:14:36.809
FOLLOWERS, 829,351,
215,231 LESS THAN YESTERDAY

00:14:36.876 --> 00:14:38.478
The tables have turned!

00:14:38.578 --> 00:14:41.214
Serves you right, you vixen.

00:14:42.081 --> 00:14:44.016
You did something, didn't you?

00:14:44.417 --> 00:14:46.352
I... I didn't do anything.

00:14:47.353 --> 00:14:49.722
Just focus on getting first place
in the debut ranking

00:14:49.789 --> 00:14:51.124
and paying off the debt.

00:14:51.224 --> 00:14:53.760
That's all you have to think about.

00:14:57.630 --> 00:14:59.365
- Have you seen this?
- TORINNER's bribery?

00:14:59.432 --> 00:15:00.767
The members were bought off, too.

00:15:00.833 --> 00:15:03.302
- The agency covered it up.
- They also have trouble with women.

00:15:03.369 --> 00:15:04.771
This is horrible.

00:15:04.837 --> 00:15:07.306
- How disappointing!
- I trusted them.

00:15:07.874 --> 00:15:08.875
There's no way TORINNER

00:15:08.941 --> 00:15:10.143
would do something so awful.

00:15:10.209 --> 00:15:11.577
Delete all the fake news!

00:15:12.712 --> 00:15:15.648
But Keiko, look at this.

00:15:18.751 --> 00:15:21.287
SO ANNOYING!

00:15:21.387 --> 00:15:22.588
Are you okay?

00:15:23.189 --> 00:15:24.690
HE SLAPPED A FAN! HORRIBLE!

00:15:24.757 --> 00:15:25.758
POOR GIRL!

00:15:25.825 --> 00:15:27.527
This has to be fake.

00:15:27.627 --> 00:15:29.128
But they have a video recording.

00:15:30.163 --> 00:15:31.664
He did hit her, didn't he?

00:15:32.298 --> 00:15:34.333
TORINNER MEMBER ASSAULTED
THE OTHER TRAINEES!

00:15:34.400 --> 00:15:36.669
YEON-WOO ABUSES HIS POWER DAILY

00:15:36.736 --> 00:15:38.137
Isn't this...

00:15:38.738 --> 00:15:39.839
going a bit too far?

00:15:43.342 --> 00:15:45.144
PRESIDENT TOMIKO

00:15:50.850 --> 00:15:52.218
It says Yeon-woo used violence.

00:15:52.285 --> 00:15:53.586
He hit a little girl.

00:15:54.320 --> 00:15:56.956
- It's all a lie.
- Of course it is.

00:15:59.826 --> 00:16:00.827
Ms. Nam.

00:16:01.627 --> 00:16:05.398
Did the TORINNER members
really do something this horrible?

00:16:07.266 --> 00:16:09.235
Is this really the time
to worry about them?

00:16:09.302 --> 00:16:11.037
Now is your chance.

00:16:11.103 --> 00:16:15.107
Ms. Park said she would crush us
by any means necessary.

00:16:15.208 --> 00:16:18.044
Get more followers
while they're occupied.

00:16:19.312 --> 00:16:23.182
Producer! Get it together.
Don't you have any good ideas?

00:16:24.116 --> 00:16:26.185
I understand, CEO.

00:16:26.252 --> 00:16:28.921
I won't let the chance slip by.

00:16:41.033 --> 00:16:42.034
Sorry, I couldn't get in touch--

00:16:42.101 --> 00:16:43.936
When will the commotion
in Japan blow over?

00:16:45.471 --> 00:16:47.540
It's all groundless fake news.

00:16:47.607 --> 00:16:49.709
It'll blow over in no time.
Please don't worry.

00:16:53.379 --> 00:16:55.047
Incompetent people deserve to die.

00:16:59.685 --> 00:17:02.388
Who set this up? Nam?

00:17:02.488 --> 00:17:06.692
I don't think Ms. Nam
is capable of doing that.

00:17:07.159 --> 00:17:10.596
I reckon a professional did it.
Someone like us, probably.

00:17:10.663 --> 00:17:13.132
Do something to stop them!
I'll pay you.

00:17:15.001 --> 00:17:18.371
It can't be stopped
at this point, Ms. Park.

00:17:19.005 --> 00:17:22.241
Our magazine will be publishing
an article about them, too.

00:17:22.308 --> 00:17:24.377
Are you betraying me
after I paid you so much?

00:17:24.477 --> 00:17:28.414
You're so naive, Ms. Genius Producer!

00:17:28.781 --> 00:17:31.884
We have to make a living, too.

00:17:32.451 --> 00:17:35.855
I'll write anything that sells.
It's only natural.

00:17:38.324 --> 00:17:40.159
- TORINNER uses violence.
- Really?

00:17:40.226 --> 00:17:42.662
- Aren't they awful?
- Is TORINNER really capable of that?

00:17:42.728 --> 00:17:44.730
- There are videos.
- Assaulting a staff member?

00:17:44.797 --> 00:17:47.466
The tables have turned unexpectedly
in the follower count contest.

00:17:47.533 --> 00:17:48.701
Their true colors have been exposed!

00:17:48.768 --> 00:17:50.536
Is this the start of their downfall?

00:17:53.072 --> 00:17:56.075
Do you think Ryo will be okay?

00:17:57.743 --> 00:18:00.246
He hasn't replied
to my calls or messages for days.

00:18:03.749 --> 00:18:06.652
Your call cannot
be answered right now.

00:18:07.186 --> 00:18:08.988
Mr. Azuma, what should we do?

00:18:10.356 --> 00:18:13.859
It's no use worrying about them.
Go to sleep.

00:18:22.068 --> 00:18:23.135
Is this it?

00:18:23.869 --> 00:18:25.738
The Premature End
of the Popular Group TORINNER

00:18:35.715 --> 00:18:37.149
Hello, Ms. Tomiko?

00:18:37.216 --> 00:18:39.251
Thanks to your cooperation

00:18:39.352 --> 00:18:41.954
my plan went smoother than expected.

00:18:43.022 --> 00:18:46.626
I think you and I can continue
to become a good team.

00:18:48.094 --> 00:18:51.731
Ms. Tomiko, you really were the one
behind the TORINNER articles.

00:18:52.365 --> 00:18:54.734
It's all thanks to your cooperation.

00:18:56.202 --> 00:18:59.538
So, what would you like
to talk about?

00:18:59.639 --> 00:19:01.474
If we put the final nail
in the coffin here

00:19:01.774 --> 00:19:04.110
TORINNER will be finished,
once and for all.

00:19:04.910 --> 00:19:08.714
To do that, it will be better
to have a credible story, right?

00:19:09.248 --> 00:19:11.117
Do you have any good information?

00:19:11.817 --> 00:19:13.419
I've told you everything.

00:19:14.553 --> 00:19:16.922
Anyway, I wasn't informed that

00:19:16.989 --> 00:19:20.026
the things I told you last time
would be spread wide and far.

00:19:21.227 --> 00:19:23.262
I think it's good enough.

00:19:23.329 --> 00:19:24.330
What?

00:19:24.930 --> 00:19:26.732
Did you just talk back to me?

00:19:26.832 --> 00:19:29.535
No! I didn't mean to talk back.

00:19:30.436 --> 00:19:32.705
But I don't have
any more information.

00:19:32.805 --> 00:19:34.140
If you have nothing

00:19:34.473 --> 00:19:36.542
then make something up.

00:19:38.277 --> 00:19:39.278
Well...

00:19:39.345 --> 00:19:41.047
You were the one who said

00:19:41.147 --> 00:19:44.717
you didn't want to lose,
and you couldn't pay off your debt.

00:19:45.217 --> 00:19:49.055
That's why I'm going out
of my way to help you.

00:19:49.689 --> 00:19:52.958
Shouldn't you at least
be a bit useful to me?

00:19:54.326 --> 00:19:57.129
Help me? I didn't ask--

00:19:57.196 --> 00:19:59.331
Hey! Don't mess with me!

00:20:21.587 --> 00:20:22.822
TORINNER Members Sighted Arguing
on the Streets

00:20:22.922 --> 00:20:24.156
Music Show Staff Reveals
TORINNER's Attitude Problem

00:20:24.256 --> 00:20:25.591
Video of TORINNER Member
Being Violent Goes Viral

00:20:31.230 --> 00:20:33.332
It's too late to back out.

00:20:33.432 --> 00:20:35.868
You are my accomplice.

00:20:36.802 --> 00:20:38.037
If you betray me

00:20:38.137 --> 00:20:41.307
I'll destroy your group next.

00:20:43.109 --> 00:20:47.379
The younger brother of TORINNER's Ryo
is in your group, right?

00:20:47.813 --> 00:20:50.983
A family member must have
many stories to tell.

00:20:51.584 --> 00:20:54.687
I want some dirt on Ryo by tomorrow.

00:20:55.154 --> 00:20:56.589
No way. I can't just--

00:20:56.689 --> 00:20:58.557
Since you're the CEO

00:20:58.624 --> 00:21:02.294
you should work hard
to pay off your debt.

00:21:02.428 --> 00:21:03.429
Right?

00:21:16.375 --> 00:21:18.244
They're taking it off.

00:21:18.310 --> 00:21:19.678
It's over for TORINNER.

00:21:26.018 --> 00:21:27.186
Ms. Tomiko.

00:21:29.088 --> 00:21:31.090
- Is your practice session over?
- Yes.

00:21:31.590 --> 00:21:33.325
Our seniors came to visit
during practice.

00:21:33.392 --> 00:21:35.394
Really? Good for you.

00:21:36.162 --> 00:21:38.564
Your group is inheriting the history

00:21:38.631 --> 00:21:41.000
and tradition of our agency.

00:21:41.100 --> 00:21:43.002
That's why you

00:21:43.068 --> 00:21:44.703
genuinely shine.

00:21:47.206 --> 00:21:52.077
Tasteless fake idols are sneaking
into our industry nowadays.

00:21:52.378 --> 00:21:54.280
We need to make them
step down from the stage.

00:21:54.914 --> 00:21:58.017
Kira Tomiko told me
to give her more gossip

00:21:58.951 --> 00:22:01.253
or she will crush NAZE next.

00:22:01.854 --> 00:22:03.656
We can't have that.

00:22:04.490 --> 00:22:05.958
What will you give her next?

00:22:07.193 --> 00:22:08.394
She told me...

00:22:09.328 --> 00:22:11.764
to make Yuya reveal Ryo's secrets.

00:22:12.765 --> 00:22:16.168
She wants our member to dig up
his own brother's scandal?

00:22:16.235 --> 00:22:17.303
I see.

00:22:18.070 --> 00:22:20.506
So, will you really make him do it?

00:22:24.109 --> 00:22:25.611
Darn it!

00:22:26.979 --> 00:22:29.248
I don't know what I should do!

00:22:32.418 --> 00:22:34.053
TORINNER must retire!

00:22:34.153 --> 00:22:35.454
- Retire!
- Retire!

00:22:35.521 --> 00:22:38.457
Come out at once! Apologize!

00:22:38.524 --> 00:22:39.525
What's going on?

00:22:39.959 --> 00:22:40.960
This is so horrible!

00:22:45.030 --> 00:22:46.098
It's Ryo!

00:22:48.100 --> 00:22:49.101
Let's go.

00:22:50.769 --> 00:22:52.838
Apologize! Come out!

00:22:52.905 --> 00:22:54.206
Hello.

00:22:54.807 --> 00:22:56.375
We finally meet.

00:22:57.243 --> 00:23:00.379
I'm sorry I haven't been able
to get in touch, Yuya.

00:23:01.046 --> 00:23:02.781
If I turn on my phone

00:23:03.949 --> 00:23:05.885
I get bombarded by prank calls.

00:23:05.985 --> 00:23:09.088
No, it's totally fine
as long as you're okay.

00:23:10.656 --> 00:23:11.857
It had to be you guys!

00:23:11.924 --> 00:23:13.659
You made them write all those lies!

00:23:13.726 --> 00:23:16.195
Do you want to win so badly
that you would go this far?

00:23:16.795 --> 00:23:19.431
Don't be ridiculous.
We didn't do anything.

00:23:20.199 --> 00:23:21.200
It's true, Yeon-woo.

00:23:24.970 --> 00:23:26.505
We're holed up in the apartment

00:23:27.873 --> 00:23:29.541
and we aren't allowed to practice.

00:23:30.709 --> 00:23:33.312
We won't be able to debut, will we?

00:23:43.222 --> 00:23:44.723
Thank you for coming.

00:23:46.258 --> 00:23:49.094
But people might talk
if you two are seen here.

00:23:49.695 --> 00:23:50.829
You had better go now.

00:23:56.936 --> 00:23:58.170
But we...

00:24:03.075 --> 00:24:05.444
The way things are going,
we feel bad for TORINNER.

00:24:05.544 --> 00:24:10.049
We want to at least debunk
the fake information.

00:24:10.115 --> 00:24:13.352
But if we leave things be,
we can win the follower contest.

00:24:13.419 --> 00:24:15.220
What if they make a comeback?

00:24:15.321 --> 00:24:17.856
Winning with all these lies
is meaningless for us!

00:24:19.158 --> 00:24:22.461
Does that mean you won't regret it

00:24:22.795 --> 00:24:24.697
if you lose the follower contest

00:24:25.497 --> 00:24:26.699
after clearing TORINNER's name?

00:24:35.941 --> 00:24:38.043
We want to compete fairly.

00:24:38.477 --> 00:24:40.079
So we want to help TORINNER!

00:24:49.588 --> 00:24:50.689
Geez.

00:24:51.623 --> 00:24:53.692
You're too nice for your own good.

00:24:53.759 --> 00:24:55.995
You guys could've won the contest!

00:24:57.162 --> 00:25:00.466
Well, Minase and I will go and ask
if our CEO concurs.

00:25:00.532 --> 00:25:02.501
You guys will wait here.

00:25:07.606 --> 00:25:10.242
This is such a headache, Ms. Nam!

00:25:10.309 --> 00:25:13.479
Our members wish to help TORINNER.

00:25:13.812 --> 00:25:16.315
They want to compete fair and square.

00:25:17.549 --> 00:25:19.985
They're so naive. It's hopeless.

00:25:20.052 --> 00:25:24.223
You were already determined to win
by any means necessary.

00:25:24.289 --> 00:25:25.424
Mr. Azuma.

00:25:30.529 --> 00:25:32.364
I didn't mean to do this.

00:25:36.268 --> 00:25:38.070
Everything happened
because of my silly mistake.

00:25:39.271 --> 00:25:40.839
I am really sorry.

00:25:44.176 --> 00:25:45.744
Please don't apologize.

00:25:49.348 --> 00:25:53.552
We know
you're doing your best for NAZE.

00:25:53.752 --> 00:25:54.953
We understand.

00:25:55.788 --> 00:25:59.825
But I feel the same as everyone.

00:26:00.893 --> 00:26:04.296
Ms. Nam, we want you
to be the CEO of NAZE

00:26:04.363 --> 00:26:08.167
the group that will win first place
fair and square.

00:26:12.638 --> 00:26:16.308
Honestly, I want that to happen, too.

00:26:18.043 --> 00:26:22.214
But now, I don't know
what I'm supposed to do.

00:26:25.784 --> 00:26:26.785
Nam.

00:26:29.154 --> 00:26:31.256
You're the captain of our ship.

00:26:31.723 --> 00:26:35.227
The direction you steer will decide
the fates of everyone on board.

00:26:36.095 --> 00:26:37.463
It's a huge responsibility.

00:26:39.631 --> 00:26:40.632
But...

00:26:42.201 --> 00:26:46.038
We've decided to follow you.

00:26:47.072 --> 00:26:48.707
If the captain makes a mistake

00:26:49.341 --> 00:26:51.176
we just need to give you
our full support.

00:26:52.111 --> 00:26:53.545
That's what friends are for.

00:26:58.050 --> 00:26:59.084
So?

00:27:01.753 --> 00:27:02.754
What will you do?

00:27:21.673 --> 00:27:23.008
Please help me.

00:27:26.078 --> 00:27:27.346
How did that go?

00:27:28.280 --> 00:27:29.648
Just as you thought.

00:27:29.715 --> 00:27:30.883
All right!

00:27:31.483 --> 00:27:33.018
What are you talking about?

00:27:33.952 --> 00:27:35.087
Let me explain.

00:27:35.587 --> 00:27:38.724
A girl was hit in the video that
accused Yeon-woo of using violence

00:27:38.790 --> 00:27:41.593
so we decided to look for her.

00:27:41.693 --> 00:27:43.562
If she's a TORINNER fan

00:27:43.629 --> 00:27:45.931
she must have attended
other events, too.

00:27:45.998 --> 00:27:47.799
So we searched
through various videos.

00:27:47.866 --> 00:27:49.468
And we were right.

00:27:49.535 --> 00:27:51.436
She was sighted
in several locations.

00:27:51.537 --> 00:27:53.972
I messaged the girl's mom

00:27:54.072 --> 00:27:55.941
and she agreed to meet me.

00:27:56.008 --> 00:27:57.176
Hello.

00:27:57.776 --> 00:27:59.244
We finally meet.

00:28:03.148 --> 00:28:04.283
Hello.

00:28:07.853 --> 00:28:11.290
At that time, my daughter got
too close to Yeon-woo

00:28:11.356 --> 00:28:13.292
and his hand touched her lightly.

00:28:13.959 --> 00:28:18.564
But someone edited the video
in a malicious way.

00:28:19.264 --> 00:28:22.968
Yeon-woo was very nice to my daughter

00:28:24.169 --> 00:28:26.572
but it turned into this whole mess.

00:28:27.940 --> 00:28:33.712
Will you join me and punish
the bad people to protect TORINNER?

00:28:39.585 --> 00:28:42.221
Her mother gave me
the contact details of her friends

00:28:42.321 --> 00:28:44.323
whose daughters
are also TORINNER's fans

00:28:44.423 --> 00:28:46.124
- and I asked them to work with us.
- Thank you.

00:28:47.693 --> 00:28:51.163
So we'll be busy starting tomorrow.

00:28:51.763 --> 00:28:53.298
Ms. Nam, please help us.

00:28:55.234 --> 00:28:57.469
Busy? What will we be doing?

00:29:07.980 --> 00:29:09.615
Why are there so many people here?

00:29:11.817 --> 00:29:13.619
They're writing messages.

00:29:14.219 --> 00:29:16.088
Mr. Azuma came up with this idea.

00:29:16.188 --> 00:29:17.189
Instead of the anonymity

00:29:17.256 --> 00:29:18.257
of social media

00:29:18.757 --> 00:29:20.325
they'll write their true feelings

00:29:20.392 --> 00:29:22.527
for TORINNER by hand.

00:29:23.895 --> 00:29:25.063
What do you think?

00:29:25.998 --> 00:29:27.065
It's awesome.

00:29:28.567 --> 00:29:30.569
Okay! I'll help, too.

00:29:31.270 --> 00:29:32.571
Good morning!

00:29:34.106 --> 00:29:35.707
Thank you!

00:29:42.314 --> 00:29:43.348
Are you okay?

00:29:45.017 --> 00:29:46.018
Are you okay?

00:29:46.652 --> 00:29:49.054
That's some nasty editing.

00:29:50.922 --> 00:29:53.825
Is that woman planning to betray me?

00:29:58.830 --> 00:30:01.566
For now, release that material.

00:30:01.967 --> 00:30:03.802
I'll get rid of TORINNER first.

00:30:17.849 --> 00:30:19.017
Seriously?

00:30:19.084 --> 00:30:20.485
Children cry easily

00:30:20.552 --> 00:30:21.553
and are difficult to deal with.

00:30:21.620 --> 00:30:23.355
That's why I hate them.

00:30:23.422 --> 00:30:25.524
They can't do anything alone.

00:30:26.925 --> 00:30:28.927
No to child abuse!

00:30:29.328 --> 00:30:30.329
No to abuse!

00:30:30.429 --> 00:30:31.463
DO NOT BULLY THE WEAK

00:30:31.530 --> 00:30:32.998
DEMONSTRATION
AGAINST TORINNER ESCALATES

00:30:33.598 --> 00:30:36.802
Goodness, that old woman
just won't give up.

00:30:36.902 --> 00:30:39.204
If it has escalated to this level

00:30:40.272 --> 00:30:42.074
those message boards
aren't going to be enough!

00:30:45.777 --> 00:30:46.812
Come in.

00:30:49.114 --> 00:30:50.282
What?

00:30:50.982 --> 00:30:52.684
Why are you at our office?

00:30:52.751 --> 00:30:53.752
Welcome.

00:30:54.553 --> 00:30:56.488
We'll hear you out first.

00:30:59.858 --> 00:31:01.760
This has been maliciously edited

00:31:01.827 --> 00:31:03.228
just like the article about the girl.

00:31:04.529 --> 00:31:07.466
He sent these messages
to cheer up a junior

00:31:07.833 --> 00:31:11.036
but they twisted it to make it
look like he hates children.

00:31:11.103 --> 00:31:13.305
Sounds like something they would do.

00:31:16.141 --> 00:31:17.376
Didn't she ask you

00:31:17.442 --> 00:31:20.979
to use Yuya to find out about
his brother's secrets the other day?

00:31:21.046 --> 00:31:23.515
She must be thinking
about fabricating a story

00:31:23.582 --> 00:31:25.350
of Ryo's younger brother
exposing his secrets.

00:31:25.650 --> 00:31:29.755
I bet she's planning to get rid of
both TORINNER and NAZE.

00:31:30.655 --> 00:31:33.825
How did she come up
with such a nasty idea?

00:31:34.025 --> 00:31:37.929
So, to fight back against that woman

00:31:38.797 --> 00:31:40.799
and to help TORINNER

00:31:41.199 --> 00:31:43.902
we'll need a temporary truce
with Ms. Park, okay?

00:31:43.969 --> 00:31:45.036
No way.

00:31:45.604 --> 00:31:47.606
There's no way
I can trust that traitor!

00:31:47.706 --> 00:31:48.907
As I've told you many times

00:31:49.207 --> 00:31:51.943
I believed in their talent.

00:31:52.010 --> 00:31:54.880
That's why I prepared the best stage
that a poor agency can't provide.

00:31:54.946 --> 00:31:56.581
- You!
- But...

00:31:57.749 --> 00:31:59.184
To be honest

00:32:00.652 --> 00:32:03.088
I didn't expect you
to be so persistent.

00:32:03.688 --> 00:32:06.625
I thought you would give up
and go bankrupt right away.

00:32:07.692 --> 00:32:08.827
Serves you right.

00:32:10.028 --> 00:32:11.563
I think I finally know

00:32:11.630 --> 00:32:14.633
why Mr. Choi Ki-young
is so wary of NAZE.

00:32:15.934 --> 00:32:17.969
Mr. Azuma's unrestrained
creative power

00:32:18.236 --> 00:32:20.739
and CEO Nam's tenacity...

00:32:21.039 --> 00:32:23.708
I assumed you
were an insignificant and weak group.

00:32:25.911 --> 00:32:27.646
But I need to change my perspective.

00:32:28.914 --> 00:32:30.315
Why are you saying that
all of a sudden?

00:32:30.382 --> 00:32:33.385
That modest attitude
isn't going to make me trust you!

00:32:33.885 --> 00:32:36.888
Ms. Park is going
to do her part properly.

00:32:36.955 --> 00:32:39.090
- That's why I asked her here.
- What do you mean?

00:32:39.157 --> 00:32:42.060
Before that, we need to call a truce.

00:32:48.967 --> 00:32:50.101
Fine!

00:32:50.802 --> 00:32:53.505
It's to defeat that
unreasonable old hag. I have to.

00:32:53.572 --> 00:32:55.607
No need to force yourself
to work with me.

00:32:55.941 --> 00:32:57.409
I can handle it myself.

00:32:57.509 --> 00:32:59.211
Look who's talking!

00:32:59.311 --> 00:33:01.246
You're two peas in a pod.

00:33:02.347 --> 00:33:05.517
Is this what they mean by
"a crayfish is the friend of a crab"?

00:33:05.584 --> 00:33:07.052
Why am I the crayfish?

00:33:07.118 --> 00:33:08.186
Come on.

00:33:08.820 --> 00:33:09.855
Here.

00:33:15.093 --> 00:33:17.729
Okay, let the battle begin!

00:33:18.430 --> 00:33:20.065
First, Ms. Park.

00:33:20.131 --> 00:33:22.033
Announce that TORINNER will hold
a press conference

00:33:22.100 --> 00:33:23.468
in front of the agency tomorrow.

00:33:23.535 --> 00:33:25.604
It's more fun
to have more spectators.

00:33:26.438 --> 00:33:27.839
Come out at once, TORINNER!

00:33:27.906 --> 00:33:29.841
Will they really hold
a press conference?

00:33:29.908 --> 00:33:31.209
- Apologize!
- Apologize!

00:33:31.276 --> 00:33:34.045
- Apologize!
- Take responsibility and explain!

00:33:36.081 --> 00:33:37.716
A press conference?

00:33:38.216 --> 00:33:40.785
It's only going to add fuel
to the fire.

00:33:41.286 --> 00:33:43.588
- Poor TORINNER.
- Retire, violent group!

00:34:24.696 --> 00:34:25.730
RYO

00:34:25.797 --> 00:34:27.465
THERE WAS NO VIOLENCE,
WE SUPPORT YOU

00:34:27.566 --> 00:34:28.900
WE'LL CONTINUE TO STAND BY TORINNER

00:34:29.000 --> 00:34:30.368
TORINNER, WE'RE ROOTING FOR YOU

00:34:30.468 --> 00:34:31.970
TORINNER IS INNOCENT!

00:34:32.070 --> 00:34:38.977
DON'T BULLY TORINNER!

00:34:46.151 --> 00:34:48.720
DON'T BULLY TORINNER!

00:34:52.290 --> 00:34:55.927
We love TORINNER!

00:34:56.928 --> 00:35:00.732
Reporters and the people
posting on social media

00:35:01.032 --> 00:35:02.467
please don't badmouth TORINNER

00:35:02.867 --> 00:35:05.203
without checking the facts properly!

00:35:05.837 --> 00:35:07.739
Please don't bully TORINNER!

00:35:10.475 --> 00:35:13.678
But didn't a TORINNER member hit you?

00:35:14.012 --> 00:35:16.147
Many people have seen that video.

00:35:16.381 --> 00:35:18.183
Even if you love them

00:35:18.283 --> 00:35:21.152
violence against children
is not okay.

00:35:32.831 --> 00:35:33.898
Are you okay?

00:35:35.400 --> 00:35:36.534
Are you okay?

00:35:36.601 --> 00:35:38.336
I walked too close to him

00:35:38.403 --> 00:35:40.372
so Yeon-woo's hand touched me.

00:35:41.072 --> 00:35:42.073
But...

00:35:43.441 --> 00:35:45.443
Yeon-woo was very nice

00:35:45.677 --> 00:35:47.078
and he apologized.

00:35:47.879 --> 00:35:49.814
He even gave me an autograph
on my handkerchief.

00:35:53.585 --> 00:35:54.653
There you go.

00:35:55.153 --> 00:35:56.488
Thank you.

00:35:56.588 --> 00:35:57.722
I'm sorry.

00:35:58.823 --> 00:36:02.127
I came to love TORINNER even more.

00:36:02.727 --> 00:36:06.898
We want everyone to know
the real TORINNER, too!

00:36:10.235 --> 00:36:11.670
Please get to know them!

00:36:12.270 --> 00:36:15.240
- Please get to know them!
- Please get to know them!

00:36:20.512 --> 00:36:22.781
I knew it.
It wasn't TORINNER's fault.

00:36:23.682 --> 00:36:25.016
I'm glad that I had faith in them.

00:36:27.752 --> 00:36:29.220
Hey, TORINNER is here!

00:36:37.962 --> 00:36:39.564
DON'T BULLY TORINNER!

00:36:46.004 --> 00:36:49.908
We are truly sorry about

00:36:51.076 --> 00:36:52.677
the commotion we caused.

00:36:53.445 --> 00:36:56.815
We regret that our actions led
to misunderstandings.

00:36:56.881 --> 00:36:58.149
NO TO VIOLENCE AGAINST CHILDREN

00:36:59.417 --> 00:37:02.787
But there's something we need
to reflect on even more deeply.

00:37:09.294 --> 00:37:11.029
Our young fans

00:37:11.496 --> 00:37:14.599
mustered all their courage
and came forward to protect us

00:37:15.767 --> 00:37:19.070
even though we should've trusted
and fought for our team member first.

00:37:21.906 --> 00:37:25.844
The children taught us
a very important lesson.

00:37:25.944 --> 00:37:27.445
DON'T BULLY TORINNER!

00:37:28.713 --> 00:37:29.714
Also...

00:37:32.650 --> 00:37:33.752
The same goes for NAZE.

00:37:34.953 --> 00:37:37.655
We're rivals that must defeat

00:37:37.722 --> 00:37:39.858
each other to survive

00:37:41.092 --> 00:37:44.362
But NAZE came here
to protect us, and...

00:37:46.698 --> 00:37:47.999
But we...

00:37:51.936 --> 00:37:52.971
are friends.

00:38:01.179 --> 00:38:02.881
They said we are their friends.

00:38:04.115 --> 00:38:08.086
So many people believe in us.

00:38:10.221 --> 00:38:12.357
That's what makes us proud.

00:38:15.493 --> 00:38:17.529
We can hold our heads high
and do our best again.

00:38:18.563 --> 00:38:21.199
Please root for us.

00:38:21.599 --> 00:38:23.034
- Please root for us!
- Please root for us!

00:38:27.539 --> 00:38:30.108
- TORINNER, do your best!
- Do your best!

00:38:30.175 --> 00:38:31.442
DON'T BULLY TORINNER!

00:38:33.778 --> 00:38:34.913
Do your best!

00:38:50.228 --> 00:38:53.531
My, fancy seeing you here!

00:38:55.400 --> 00:38:56.668
Now that you've defied me

00:38:57.068 --> 00:39:00.038
do you think you can survive
in showbiz in Japan?

00:39:00.672 --> 00:39:03.541
Oh, no! I wouldn't dream
of doing that.

00:39:04.809 --> 00:39:10.582
But I was curious about the person
who edited that video of Yeon-woo

00:39:10.648 --> 00:39:12.217
so I looked into the account.

00:39:12.517 --> 00:39:16.087
Turns out that the same person
also streams your idols' videos.

00:39:16.287 --> 00:39:17.288
That means...

00:39:17.355 --> 00:39:20.258
Wait! The person
who made that malicious video was...

00:39:20.358 --> 00:39:23.828
No way, could that be someone
from Kira Production?

00:39:24.195 --> 00:39:27.165
Come on. That can't be, right?

00:39:30.001 --> 00:39:31.769
Don't mess with us!

00:39:33.271 --> 00:39:35.974
I don't know
what you're talking about.

00:39:36.040 --> 00:39:37.175
You'll have to excuse me.

00:39:39.477 --> 00:39:42.447
Stop scheming
with your petty little tricks!

00:39:42.547 --> 00:39:44.716
You idiot!

00:39:45.250 --> 00:39:46.918
Thank you, everyone!

00:39:46.985 --> 00:39:49.888
- I knew TORINNER was good.
- Who spread the fake news?

00:39:49.954 --> 00:39:52.023
- It was a misunderstanding.
- Sorry that I doubted you.

00:39:52.090 --> 00:39:54.158
- TORINNER is the best!
- I'm rooting for you!

00:39:54.225 --> 00:39:56.728
- TORINNER is the best!
- I love their friendship with NAZE!

00:39:56.794 --> 00:39:58.830
I'm looking forward
to the follower contest!

00:40:00.098 --> 00:40:01.099
Man...

00:40:01.633 --> 00:40:04.469
I wish I had crushed those guys.

00:40:06.237 --> 00:40:08.139
In the follower count contest

00:40:08.206 --> 00:40:09.741
between K-pop's
promising rookies, TORINNER

00:40:09.807 --> 00:40:11.109
and the new group, NAZE

00:40:11.175 --> 00:40:16.147
it's finally time
to announce the results!

00:40:17.248 --> 00:40:21.085
There is only one simple rule,
and that is

00:40:21.152 --> 00:40:22.754
the loser must do anything
the winner says.

00:40:22.854 --> 00:40:26.758
Now, let's have a look at
the follower counts for both groups!

00:40:26.824 --> 00:40:28.993
Here are the results!

00:40:32.997 --> 00:40:33.998
Go!

00:40:35.266 --> 00:40:36.267
Keep going!

00:40:40.104 --> 00:40:44.943
RESULTS

00:40:45.043 --> 00:40:47.712
By a slight margin,
the winner is TORINNER!

00:40:48.313 --> 00:40:49.447
It's over.

00:40:50.048 --> 00:40:55.386
What will TORINNER, the winner,
make NAZE, the loser, do?

00:40:55.653 --> 00:40:58.122
This is a turning point
in their lives.

00:40:58.189 --> 00:40:59.190
Here you go.

00:41:01.960 --> 00:41:04.062
There's no point panicking now.

00:41:05.596 --> 00:41:06.597
Bring it on!

00:41:08.199 --> 00:41:11.302
Now, I'll announce
my request for NAZE.

00:41:11.402 --> 00:41:12.470
TORINNER WINS

00:41:12.537 --> 00:41:13.538
I would like NAZE...

00:41:19.644 --> 00:41:24.749
to continue
to be TORINNER's rival in good faith.

00:41:32.290 --> 00:41:33.291
Is that all?

00:41:36.160 --> 00:41:38.663
Thank goodness!

00:41:44.869 --> 00:41:48.106
Amazing, TORINNER!
What wonderful sportsmanship!

00:41:48.172 --> 00:41:49.173
I'm touched!

00:41:56.714 --> 00:41:59.517
Did you two just exchange glances?

00:41:59.584 --> 00:42:00.585
What was that about?

00:42:00.651 --> 00:42:02.487
It means she has returned the favor.

00:42:03.121 --> 00:42:04.622
The real competition begins now.

00:42:15.466 --> 00:42:17.368
We'll aim for MAMA's
Best New Artist Award.

00:42:17.468 --> 00:42:19.437
- We can get it!
- Yes!

00:42:19.737 --> 00:42:20.738
Okay, guys!

00:42:21.672 --> 00:42:22.940
Let's go!

00:42:23.007 --> 00:42:24.942
- Yes!
- Yes!

00:42:26.611 --> 00:42:29.113
This time, we'll make it to MAMA.

00:42:30.548 --> 00:42:32.483
MAMA? What do you mean?

00:42:32.550 --> 00:42:34.385
Azuma, what did you just say?

00:42:34.452 --> 00:42:35.686
I said

00:42:36.154 --> 00:42:38.790
I'll take them to MAMA this time.

00:42:42.026 --> 00:42:44.095
You mean that promise
you failed to fulfill?

00:42:46.464 --> 00:42:48.733
Let's do this, Azuma.

00:42:54.372 --> 00:42:56.174
You lied to me again.

00:42:57.341 --> 00:42:58.376
I'm sorry.

00:42:58.443 --> 00:42:59.444
You're sorry?

00:42:59.510 --> 00:43:02.280
They'll be making their
important debut in Japan soon.

00:43:02.647 --> 00:43:06.717
I'm surprised that they're competing
on the same level

00:43:06.784 --> 00:43:08.119
as that group of leftovers.

00:43:08.953 --> 00:43:11.255
Is this a nightmare?

00:43:16.928 --> 00:43:19.564
Incompetent people
like you don't deserve a future.

00:43:23.634 --> 00:43:24.635
Get out.

00:43:25.536 --> 00:43:26.737
Work until you drop.

00:43:27.472 --> 00:43:28.873
Get out!

00:43:41.185 --> 00:43:43.821
THIS DRAMA IS FICTIONAL

00:43:44.422 --> 00:43:45.656
It gave me a really bad burn.

00:43:45.723 --> 00:43:47.125
One million yen in medical expenses.

00:43:47.225 --> 00:43:48.826
If people find out,
it'll cause a stir.

00:43:48.926 --> 00:43:51.295
We've been working so hard.
I'm sorry, everyone.

00:43:51.362 --> 00:43:53.231
I found a good story about NAZE.

00:43:53.297 --> 00:43:55.500
I think he should leave the industry.

00:43:55.566 --> 00:43:56.868
Will we really be able to debut?

00:43:56.968 --> 00:43:58.836
I'm under pressure, too!